President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Alaska due to a severe storm that occurred from September 28 to September 30, 2017. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the North Slope Borough, including funding for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also receive federal funding. Thomas J. Dargan has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and additional designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.